    Performs a bitwise And operation.

    public static object BitAndObj (object obj1, object obj2);

    Parameters

    • obj1
      System.Object

      Required. Any Boolean or numeric expression.

    • obj2
      System.Object

      Required. Any Boolean or numeric expression.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      1 if both obj1 and obj2 evaluate to 1; otherwise, 0.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

  • BitOrObj(Object,Object)

    Performs a bitwise Or operation.

    public static object BitOrObj (object obj1, object obj2);

    Parameters

    • obj1
      System.Object

      Required. Any Boolean or numeric expression.

    • obj2
      System.Object

      Required. Any Boolean or numeric expression.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      0 if both obj1 and obj2 evaluate to 0; otherwise, 1.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

  • BitXorObj(Object,Object)

    Performs an Xor operation.

    public static object BitXorObj (object obj1, object obj2);

    Parameters

    • obj1
      System.Object

      Required. Any Boolean or numeric expression.

    • obj2
      System.Object

      Required. Any Boolean or numeric expression.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      A numeric value that represents the bitwise exclusion (exclusive bitwise disjunction) of two numeric bit patterns. For more information, see Xor Operator.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

      System.Object

      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

      The full quotient of o1 divided by o2, including any remainder.

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

    public static object GetObjectValuePrimitive (object o);

    • o
      System.Object

      Required. Any expression.

      The primitive value of o typed as object.

  • IDivObj(Object,Object)

    Performs an integer division (\) operation.

    public static object IDivObj (object o1, object o2);

    Parameters

    • o1
      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

    • o2
      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      The integer quotient of o1 divided by o2, which discards any remainder and retains only the integer portion.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

  • LikeObj(Object,Object,CompareMethod)

    Performs a Like comparison.

    public static bool LikeObj (object vLeft, object vRight, Microsoft.VisualBasic.CompareMethod CompareOption);

    Parameters

    • vLeft
      System.Object

      Required. Any expression.

    • vRight
      System.Object

      Required. Any string expression conforming to the pattern-matching conventions described in Like Operator.

    • CompareOption
      CompareMethod

      Required. A CompareMethod value that specifies that the operation use either text or binary comparison.

    Returns

    • Boolean

      True if the string representation of the value in vLeft satisfies the pattern that is contained in vRight; otherwise, False. True if both vLeft and vRight are Nothing.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

    • o1
      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      The remainder after o1 is divided by o2.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

    Performs a unary minus (–) operation.

    public static object NegObj (object obj);

    Parameters

    • obj
      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      The negative value of obj.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

  • NotObj(Object)

    Performs a Not operation.

    public static object NotObj (object obj);

    Parameters

    • obj
      System.Object

      Required. Any Boolean or numeric expression.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      For Boolean operations, False if obj is True; otherwise, True. For bitwise operations, 1 if obj is 0; otherwise, 0.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

  • ObjTst(Object,Object,Boolean)

    Performs binary or text string comparison when given two objects.

    public static int ObjTst (object o1, object o2, bool TextCompare);

    Parameters

    • o1
      System.Object

      Required. Any expression.

    • o2
      System.Object

      Required. Any expression.

    • TextCompare
      Boolean

      Required. True to perform a case-insensitive string comparison; otherwise, False.

    Returns

    • Int32
      Value
      		 Condition
      -1
      		 o1 is less than o2.
      0
      		 o1 is equal to o2.
      1
      		 o1 is greater than o2.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

  • PlusObj(Object)

    Performs a unary plus (+) operation.

    public static object PlusObj (object obj);

    Parameters

    • obj
      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      The value of obj. (The sign of the obj is unchanged.)

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

  • PowObj(Object,Object)

    Performs an exponent (^) operation.

    public static object PowObj (object obj1, object obj2);

    Parameters

    • obj1
      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

    • obj2
      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      The result of obj1 raised to the power of obj2.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

  • ShiftLeftObj(Object,Int32)

    Performs an arithmetic left shift (<<) operation.

    public static object ShiftLeftObj (object o1, int amount);

    Parameters

    • o1
      System.Object

      Required. Integral numeric expression. The bit pattern to be shifted. The data type must be an integral type (SByte, Byte, Short, UShort, Integer, UInteger, Long, or ULong).

    • amount
      Int32

      Required. Numeric expression. The number of bits to shift the bit pattern. The data type must be Integer or widen to Integer.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      An integral numeric value. The result of shifting the bit pattern. The data type is the same as that of o1.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

  • ShiftRightObj(Object,Int32)

    Performs an arithmetic right shift (>>) operation.

    public static object ShiftRightObj (object o1, int amount);

    Parameters

    • o1
      System.Object

      Required. Integral numeric expression. The bit pattern to be shifted. The data type must be an integral type (SByte, Byte, Short, UShort, Integer, UInteger, Long, or ULong).

    • amount
      Int32

      Required. Numeric expression. The number of bits to shift the bit pattern. The data type must be Integer or widen to Integer.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      An integral numeric value. The result of shifting the bit pattern. The data type is the same as that of o1.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

  • StrCatObj(Object,Object)

    Performs a string concatenation (&) operation.

    public static object StrCatObj (object vLeft, object vRight);

    Parameters

    • vLeft
      System.Object

      Required. Any expression.

    • vRight
      System.Object

      Required. Any expression.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      A string representing the concatenation of vLeft and vRight.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

  • SubObj(Object,Object)

    Performs a subtraction (–) operation.

    public static object SubObj (object o1, object o2);

    Parameters

    • o1
      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

    • o2
      System.Object

      Required. Any numeric expression.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      The difference between o1 and o2.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.

  • XorObj(Object,Object)

    Performs an Xor comparison.

    public static object XorObj (object obj1, object obj2);

    Parameters

    • obj1
      System.Object

      Required. Any Boolean or numeric expression.

    • obj2
      System.Object

      Required. Any Boolean or numeric expression.

    Returns

    • System.Object

      A Boolean or numeric value. For a Boolean comparison, the return value is the logical exclusion (exclusive logical disjunction) of two Boolean values. For bitwise (numeric) operations, the return value is a numeric value that represents the bitwise exclusion (exclusive bitwise disjunction) of two numeric bit patterns. For more information, see Xor Operator.

    Remarks

    This class supports the Visual Basic compiler and is not intended to be used directly from your code.
